WEBVTT

00:01.752 --> 00:03.212
Mr. and Mrs. DiMeo?

00:03.212 --> 00:04.213
Anyone home?

00:04.213 --> 00:05.380
[ "Born To Be Wild" plays ]

00:05.380 --> 00:06.465
Oh, no.
Yes!

00:06.465 --> 00:07.382
What?

00:07.382 --> 00:08.592
It's happening!
It's happening.

00:08.592 --> 00:09.384
What is?

00:09.384 --> 00:11.011
Just listen
to the lyrics.

00:11.011 --> 00:14.139
♪ Get your wheelchair van
a‐runnin' ♪

00:14.139 --> 00:17.726
♪ Annual DiMeo road trip ♪

00:17.726 --> 00:20.896
♪ Nothing planned in advance ♪

00:20.896 --> 00:22.773
♪ And the song doesn't rhyme ♪

00:22.773 --> 00:24.149
A trip?
Holiday break ends tomorrow.

00:24.149 --> 00:25.484
Wait for it.

00:25.484 --> 00:28.695
♪ Early January's
the cheapest time to travel ♪

00:28.695 --> 00:30.739
♪ Jimmy heard that once
and treats it as a fact ♪

00:30.739 --> 00:31.990
What about school?

00:31.990 --> 00:35.035
♪ Who cares
if you miss some school? ♪

00:35.035 --> 00:37.663
♪ It's only second grade ♪

00:37.663 --> 00:39.873
Not true anymore.
In high school now. It matters.

00:39.873 --> 00:44.086
♪ Ray objects every year ♪

00:46.046 --> 00:51.635
♪ Ray objects every year ♪

00:51.635 --> 00:53.512
You don't know
that I object every year.

00:53.512 --> 00:54.846
Come on, man,
you know you do.

01:00.519 --> 01:03.063
Thank you for agreeing
to house‐sit, Kenneth.

01:03.063 --> 01:04.356
Thanks for hinting
you'd pay me,

01:04.356 --> 01:05.566
then backing off of it

01:05.566 --> 01:07.693
resulting in
this uncomfortable moment.

01:09.152 --> 01:10.612
Right.

01:10.612 --> 01:12.823
Make sure the windows
and the doors are locked.

01:12.823 --> 01:15.534
And you'll notice there are
plants there, there, and there.

01:15.534 --> 01:18.203
Mm‐hmm. Bring those
back to life. Got it.

01:18.203 --> 01:19.246
So, this trip of yours ‐‐

01:19.246 --> 01:20.497
there's really
no planning at all?

01:20.497 --> 01:21.915
None.

01:21.915 --> 01:23.584
We get in the car,
decide left or right,

01:23.584 --> 01:24.876
and drive.

01:24.876 --> 01:26.003
Never know
where we're gonna end up.

01:26.003 --> 01:27.546
A seaside resort,
a national park ‐‐

01:27.546 --> 01:28.922
An industrial pig farm.

01:28.922 --> 01:30.382
They let me ride one.

01:30.382 --> 01:32.509
They were so confused
as to why we were there.

01:32.509 --> 01:34.553
I have no beef
with vacations.

01:34.553 --> 01:35.512
You know that.

01:35.512 --> 01:37.055
But let's <i>plan</i> one.

01:37.055 --> 01:39.933
Make some reservations,
get some confirmation numbers.

01:39.933 --> 01:42.853
"Z as in Zebra,
7, 2, 5, Lima."

01:42.853 --> 01:44.646
Wouldn't you love
to write that down?

01:44.646 --> 01:46.606
Darling, you have to learn
to let go.

01:46.606 --> 01:48.608
Embrace spontaneity.

01:48.608 --> 01:51.278
Be open, and this year's road
trip could be the best one ever.

01:51.278 --> 01:53.322
Fine. I'll try.
Really?

01:53.322 --> 01:54.656
Oh, I was just trying
to start an argument.

01:54.656 --> 01:55.907
Okay, great.

01:55.907 --> 01:57.909
Hey, uh, leave room
to bring me something back.

01:57.909 --> 02:00.037
[ Chuckles ]
Tell him, JJ.

02:00.037 --> 02:01.371
S‐O...

02:01.371 --> 02:04.041
"Souvenirs...
are for suckers."

02:04.041 --> 02:06.835
Mm. Or for kids who moved a lot
and found peace

02:06.835 --> 02:08.628
within the imagined world
of a snow globe.

02:08.628 --> 02:10.255
Maya:
Oh, that's Jimmy's thing.

02:10.255 --> 02:12.507
He refuses to be a "pawn"
of the travel industry.

02:12.507 --> 02:14.968
The second they see tourists,
they jack up the prices,

02:14.968 --> 02:16.345
and I don't play that game.

02:16.345 --> 02:18.180
And this year, they are not
gonna see a dime from us.

02:18.180 --> 02:20.891
You want a soda? Here.

02:20.891 --> 02:23.060
You want
a souvenir T‐shirt?

02:26.313 --> 02:27.105
Here.

02:28.649 --> 02:30.067
"Somewhere"?

02:30.067 --> 02:31.318
It's a little slice
of paradise.

02:31.318 --> 02:32.361
Got to see it
before you die.

02:34.071 --> 02:35.447
Okay, kids,
first intersection.

02:35.447 --> 02:36.907
Which way do we go?

02:36.907 --> 02:38.825
[ Horn honks ]
Go around!
I'm being delightful!

02:38.825 --> 02:40.494
Right.

02:40.494 --> 02:41.495
Left.

02:41.495 --> 02:42.663
And JJ says left.

02:42.663 --> 02:44.456
Lefts have it.

02:44.456 --> 02:45.999
So you guys are gonna gang up
against me this whole trip?

02:47.417 --> 02:48.251
Right.

02:49.753 --> 02:52.547
Kenneth.
You look... different.

02:52.547 --> 02:55.676
Oh, well, because there's
none of T‐H‐I ‐‐ "this."

02:55.676 --> 02:56.802
[ Laughs ]
Oh.

02:56.802 --> 02:58.387
Without JJ ‐‐
[ Groans ]

02:58.387 --> 02:59.971
... yeah, I'm like
2 1/2 feet taller.

02:59.971 --> 03:01.932
Kind of scary up here.

03:01.932 --> 03:04.226
If JJ's out,
why are <i>you</i> at school?

03:04.226 --> 03:06.144
Oh, to take notes.

03:06.144 --> 03:07.604
JJ shouldn't
stop learning

03:07.604 --> 03:09.398
just because the DiMeos
are on vacation.

03:09.398 --> 03:11.650
Mrs. DiMeo told me
there was a death in the family.

03:11.650 --> 03:13.860
Oh.

03:13.860 --> 03:15.987
Uh... uh...

03:15.987 --> 03:18.073
Screw it. She's gone.
She lied.

03:18.073 --> 03:20.158
Unlimited refills
for life.

03:20.158 --> 03:21.785
Thank you,
Breakfast Barn.

03:21.785 --> 03:22.911
How's it taste?

03:22.911 --> 03:24.079
[ Sighs ] free.

03:24.079 --> 03:25.080
Where to next?

03:25.080 --> 03:26.832
Guys!
You won't believe it!

03:26.832 --> 03:28.875
We've happened upon
my favorite thing.

03:28.875 --> 03:29.584
Not a craft fair.

03:29.584 --> 03:31.420
A craft fair!

03:31.420 --> 03:33.672
There were two separate stands
selling soap,

03:33.672 --> 03:35.841
and that was just
in the first row I could see.

03:35.841 --> 03:38.760
Don't drag me there!
There's nothing there for me!

03:38.760 --> 03:40.095
I'll just be bored and ‐‐

03:40.095 --> 03:41.263
There's vintage comic books.

03:41.263 --> 03:42.305
They have vintage what,
now?

03:42.305 --> 03:43.682
♪♪

03:43.682 --> 03:46.560
Oh... my... God.

03:46.560 --> 03:48.186
So, Ray, was I right?

03:48.186 --> 03:50.188
I'll give it to you.
Oh!

03:50.188 --> 03:52.732
Random chance worked out
this <i>one</i> time.

03:52.732 --> 03:54.317
Excuse me.

03:54.317 --> 03:56.778
Do you have Volume 1
of "Mother Knows Best"?

03:56.778 --> 03:58.029
[ Laughs ]

03:58.029 --> 03:59.656
I'm sorry.
I don't know comic books.

03:59.656 --> 04:01.074
I'm just watching this booth
for a friend.

04:01.074 --> 04:01.992
Let me call him.

04:01.992 --> 04:04.244
No, this is <i>my</i> moment.

04:04.244 --> 04:06.079
You've made it
unnecessarily complicated.

04:06.079 --> 04:08.290
[ Eerie music plays ]

04:08.290 --> 04:10.959
<i>[ Laughs ]</i>
Can you believe some dodos
actually fall for this?

04:10.959 --> 04:12.586
Hey. Predict <i>this.</i>

04:14.588 --> 04:15.630
Dummy.

04:15.630 --> 04:16.965
<i>[ Laughs ]</i>

04:21.428 --> 04:24.055
"You will be blessed
with abundance."

04:24.055 --> 04:25.974
Ooh!
I know vocab words.

04:28.727 --> 04:31.188
<i>[ Laughs ]</i>

04:37.277 --> 04:40.405
Okay, Raja.
You've got my attention.

04:40.405 --> 04:41.823
What?

04:41.823 --> 04:43.909
I'm just gonna
throw these away.

04:43.909 --> 04:45.619
Don't judge me.

04:45.619 --> 04:47.329
<i>[ Laughs ]</i>

04:47.329 --> 04:49.331
Oh! Hey, guys.

04:49.331 --> 04:50.874
[ Chuckles ]
How we doing?

04:50.874 --> 04:52.209
Fine.
Yeah.

04:52.209 --> 04:53.585
I thought
JJ was out today.

04:53.585 --> 04:55.337
Oh, he is.

04:55.337 --> 04:57.214
Hey, so, how'd your date
with Simone go?

04:57.214 --> 04:59.049
Were her parents gone,
like you thought?

04:59.049 --> 05:00.592
They <i>were,</i> actually.
Yeah?

05:00.592 --> 05:02.427
She was ‐‐

05:02.427 --> 05:03.929
Wait.

05:03.929 --> 05:05.305
Are <i>you</i> asking or JJ?

05:05.305 --> 05:08.058
Well, I ‐‐
I guess <i>I</i> am.

05:08.058 --> 05:09.309
Is that weird?

05:10.769 --> 05:12.062
I think it might be.

05:13.146 --> 05:15.398
[ Chuckles ] Yeah,
take JJ out of this dynamic,

05:15.398 --> 05:17.484
and it's kind of weird you guys
want to hang out with me.

05:17.484 --> 05:18.902
No offense, guys.

05:18.902 --> 05:20.278
I'll take a rain check,
all right?

05:20.278 --> 05:24.533
[ Laughing ]

05:24.533 --> 05:27.494
Come on, craft fair!
5 bucks for cotton candy.

05:27.494 --> 05:30.247
This was in our freezer,
and it's all free.

05:30.247 --> 05:32.707
We got some corn dogs,
nice burritos,

05:32.707 --> 05:33.959
couple pizzas ‐‐

05:33.959 --> 05:35.126
Could I get two waters?

05:35.126 --> 05:37.462
I'm sorry?
Two waters. How much?

05:37.462 --> 05:39.673
Oh, uh...

05:39.673 --> 05:41.466
Uh, that'll be...

05:41.466 --> 05:43.593
$6.

05:43.593 --> 05:44.886
Freaking tourist markups.

05:46.972 --> 05:48.974
Thank you.
Come again?

05:48.974 --> 05:50.725
♪♪

05:50.725 --> 05:53.311
[ Sighs ]

05:53.311 --> 05:54.479
If we sell
some of this stuff,

05:54.479 --> 05:56.189
we're not just gonna
break even on this trip ‐‐

05:56.189 --> 05:58.191
We're gonna
turn a profit.

05:58.191 --> 06:00.819
"It's mostly crap."

06:00.819 --> 06:02.904
JJ, this is a craft fair.

06:02.904 --> 06:04.990
<i>Everything</i> is crap!

06:04.990 --> 06:07.909
Guys, would you consider this
a long journey

06:07.909 --> 06:09.286
with the people
closest to me?

06:11.997 --> 06:13.957
What?
I know it's fake.

06:13.957 --> 06:16.376
Well, I don't care
for your tone, JJ.

06:16.376 --> 06:19.129
Okay.
Where to next?

06:19.129 --> 06:20.422
Can we turn on
the radio?

06:20.422 --> 06:21.673
[ Click ]

06:21.673 --> 06:23.592
<i>♪ I'll get over you ♪</i>

06:23.592 --> 06:24.968
Oh, my God!
It's a sign!

06:24.968 --> 06:26.261
What do you hear?

06:26.261 --> 06:28.930
"A really old song."

06:28.930 --> 06:30.849
Who's it by?
Mozart?

06:30.849 --> 06:33.143
British pop duo Go West.

06:33.143 --> 06:34.811
Sounds like
we're going west.

06:34.811 --> 06:35.896
<i>♪ 'Cause I'm the king of ‐‐ ♪</i>

06:35.896 --> 06:36.938
West is the other way.

06:36.938 --> 06:38.231
Hold on.
[ Tires screech ]

06:38.231 --> 06:39.691
Ray:
That was close.

06:39.691 --> 06:42.444
We almost went in
a different random direction.

06:42.444 --> 06:45.405
Tell me these are not
the most delicious strawberries

06:45.405 --> 06:46.489
you've ever had.

06:46.489 --> 06:47.657
I mean,
you can't plan that.

06:47.657 --> 06:48.450
They're fine.

06:48.450 --> 06:50.285
Mmm!

06:50.285 --> 06:51.870
This one's even better.
Here. Mm.

06:51.870 --> 06:53.538
Taste this one.
I'm not doing that.
I'm not doing that.

06:53.538 --> 06:54.873
Just have it.
No.

06:54.873 --> 06:57.292
Anybody want to try my corn dog?
It's almost thawed.

06:57.292 --> 06:59.961
[ Crunches ]
Ray, you have to
open yourself up

06:59.961 --> 07:01.546
and let things happen.

07:01.546 --> 07:04.257
Magical,
wonderful things ‐‐

07:04.257 --> 07:07.260
[ Gasps ] Oh, my God!
What's that?!

07:07.260 --> 07:08.970
I think we know
what we have to do.

07:10.347 --> 07:11.389
Follow that thing.
Eat that th‐‐

07:11.389 --> 07:12.682
Follow that thing.

07:16.394 --> 07:21.358
♪♪

07:21.358 --> 07:23.902
Jimmy:
Where... are we?

07:23.902 --> 07:25.528
This is beautiful.

07:25.528 --> 07:26.863
Look.

07:26.863 --> 07:29.115
"A handsome man
will show you the way."

07:29.115 --> 07:30.825
Certainly handsome.

07:30.825 --> 07:32.202
Let's look at
the undercarriage.

07:34.245 --> 07:35.580
That's a man,
all right.

07:35.580 --> 07:36.456
[ Snorts ]

07:36.456 --> 07:37.791
Three for three, Raja.

07:37.791 --> 07:39.459
We would like
to check in, sir.

07:39.459 --> 07:40.251
[ Snorts ]

07:41.544 --> 07:43.380
Whoa, Ray!

07:43.380 --> 07:46.257
"Steps from
the Bremel Observatory."

07:46.257 --> 07:48.718
This inn is
right next to a nerdy space,

07:48.718 --> 07:49.761
and you love those.

07:49.761 --> 07:50.845
Whoa!

07:50.845 --> 07:52.472
Isn't it amazing?

07:52.472 --> 07:56.476
A donkey/llama‐y thing
brought us to literal paradise.

07:56.476 --> 07:59.145
I have to admit, it <i>has</i> been
a pretty awesome day.

07:59.145 --> 08:00.897
Wait, are you saying
I'm right?

08:00.897 --> 08:02.440
It's not about
right or wrong.

08:02.440 --> 08:03.942
No, it's about right.

08:03.942 --> 08:04.943
Which I am.

08:04.943 --> 08:06.778
And wrong ‐‐ <i>you.</i>

08:06.778 --> 08:08.154
We were having
a nice time.

08:08.154 --> 08:09.614
Let's ‐‐
[ Clears throat ]

08:09.614 --> 08:12.951
[ To tune of "Born To Be Wild" ]
♪ Mommy was right ♪

08:13.993 --> 08:16.621
♪ Mommy was right ♪

08:16.621 --> 08:17.914
All right,
that's enough!

08:17.914 --> 08:20.083
I did it. It was me.

08:20.083 --> 08:22.752
I planned
every second of this day.

08:22.752 --> 08:26.089
Gloat no more.
<i>I</i> was the right one.

08:26.089 --> 08:28.758
Sing for <i>me!</i>

08:28.758 --> 08:29.968
[ Pounding on wall ]

08:29.968 --> 08:31.636
Sorry.
Triumphant moment.

08:33.012 --> 08:35.765
You...planned us
getting <i>here?</i>

08:35.765 --> 08:37.308
We took random turns.

08:37.308 --> 08:38.518
It was fate.

08:38.518 --> 08:40.687
Let me introduce myself ‐‐
Fate.

08:40.687 --> 08:42.397
Please.

08:42.397 --> 08:44.315
Every time
you suggested a turn,

08:44.315 --> 08:45.734
we went
in the opposite direction.

08:45.734 --> 08:47.235
As you always do.

08:47.235 --> 08:47.986
Right!

08:47.986 --> 08:48.737
Left.

08:48.737 --> 08:50.030
And JJ says left.

08:50.030 --> 08:51.114
Lefts have it.

08:52.782 --> 08:54.284
[ Laughs evilly ]

08:54.284 --> 08:55.952
But that only explains
one turn.

08:55.952 --> 08:57.829
What about
the comic book place?

08:57.829 --> 08:59.873
We only went there
'cause I found the craft fair.

08:59.873 --> 09:03.710
And why were we parked
anywhere near said craft fair?

09:06.337 --> 09:07.547
Whoa, whoa, whoa!
What are you doing?

09:07.547 --> 09:08.840
Tidying up the car.

09:08.840 --> 09:10.675
Found this old thing
stuck under a seat.

09:10.675 --> 09:14.262
[ Scoffs ] That old thing
gets me free refills for life.

09:14.262 --> 09:16.431
In fact, we're probably
gonna pass a Breakfast Barn
on this trip.

09:16.431 --> 09:17.640
This is coming with us.

09:18.933 --> 09:20.185
[ Laughs evilly ]

09:22.645 --> 09:24.814
Dear God.
I'm starting to believe him.

09:24.814 --> 09:28.943
"We T‐U...
turned because of that song."

09:28.943 --> 09:30.111
Boom shakalaka!

09:30.111 --> 09:31.488
Aah!

09:31.488 --> 09:32.822
Ow!

09:32.822 --> 09:36.326
"King of Wishful Thinking" ‐‐
Go West.

09:36.326 --> 09:38.578
And then I led us
to the fruit stand,

09:38.578 --> 09:40.580
where I knew
we would see Cotton Ball,

09:40.580 --> 09:42.582
the local
celebrity alpaca.

09:42.582 --> 09:45.043
I knew you guys couldn't resist
following back to its home

09:45.043 --> 09:46.920
at this very hotel.

09:46.920 --> 09:48.713
You dragged an alpaca
into this?

09:48.713 --> 09:50.215
But you <i>didn't</i> plan
to stay here.

09:50.215 --> 09:52.675
We only got a room
'cause someone canceled
at the last min‐‐

09:52.675 --> 09:54.803
No.

09:54.803 --> 09:57.347
It doesn't go this deep.

09:57.347 --> 09:59.015
Ray: Sorry. I'm gonna
have to cancel my room.

10:00.683 --> 10:03.478
I hope to make it there
sometime in the future, too.

10:05.271 --> 10:07.148
[ Laughs evilly ]

10:07.148 --> 10:09.234
That's right.

10:09.234 --> 10:12.237
A wonderful day ‐‐
all planned.

10:12.237 --> 10:14.948
The only thing off the cuff
is this speech, and, you know,

10:14.948 --> 10:19.494
it's still, you know,
kind of...I think...very great.

10:19.494 --> 10:21.788
Well,
congratulations, Ray.

10:21.788 --> 10:22.956
You win.

10:22.956 --> 10:24.582
We <i>all</i> do.

10:24.582 --> 10:28.044
So many great things
<i>not</i> planned for tomorrow.

10:28.044 --> 10:29.504
I'm off
to the observatory.

10:29.504 --> 10:31.047
You guys might want
to get some sleep.

10:31.047 --> 10:32.340
I call the couch.

10:32.340 --> 10:33.508
I get the couch!

10:38.388 --> 10:40.723
[ Laughs evilly ]

10:40.723 --> 10:41.975
Yeah, man.

10:41.975 --> 10:43.518
Can I help you?

10:43.518 --> 10:45.812
Oh, yeah,
I'm, uh, JJ DiMeo's aide.

10:45.812 --> 10:48.064
I, uh, usually eat
with him and the kids,

10:48.064 --> 10:49.649
but he's not here today,
so I'm just gonna...

10:49.649 --> 10:51.943
This is actually
the teachers lounge.

10:51.943 --> 10:54.571
I‐I...give JJ
lots of knowledge,

10:54.571 --> 10:57.157
so I'm, you know,
basically a teacher.

10:57.157 --> 10:59.951
It's not
the basically‐a‐teachers lounge.

10:59.951 --> 11:01.494
Okay, then.

11:01.494 --> 11:02.954
For what it's worth,

11:02.954 --> 11:06.082
when the 15‐year‐olds
rejected me, they were nicer.

11:08.293 --> 11:09.419
Bunch of stuff today.

11:09.419 --> 11:10.420
Hey!

11:10.420 --> 11:12.755
Oh, well, well,
look who's back.

11:12.755 --> 11:14.799
Ralph: Didn't you used to be
the groundskeeper?

11:14.799 --> 11:17.343
It's been a while since we've
seen you in the chairs room.

11:17.343 --> 11:20.221
Well [Laughs]
it's good to be back.

11:20.221 --> 11:22.557
Are these 300 seats taken?

11:22.557 --> 11:25.143
Sit anywhere you want,
Mr. President.

11:25.143 --> 11:26.853
W‐What is that, now?

11:26.853 --> 11:29.898
Well, it's just you're not
wearing a name tag anymore.

11:29.898 --> 11:31.357
Like the president.

11:31.357 --> 11:34.694
Guys, can I just please
sit and eat this?

11:34.694 --> 11:36.237
It was bad
when it was hot.

11:36.237 --> 11:38.531
Oh, perhaps you should
veto it.

11:38.531 --> 11:39.908
[ Laughter ]

11:39.908 --> 11:42.243
Okay. Yeah, I get it.

11:42.243 --> 11:44.370
You know what?
For the record ‐‐

11:44.370 --> 11:46.706
I tried and failed to fit in
two other places

11:46.706 --> 11:48.583
before I didn't
fit in <i>here.</i>

11:48.583 --> 11:50.877
You all suck,
and I approve this message.

11:50.877 --> 11:51.961
[ Clatter ]

11:51.961 --> 11:53.463
[ Laughter ]

11:53.463 --> 11:55.215
Jimmy: Good morning, JJ.

11:55.215 --> 11:57.800
I just paid
the hotel bill.

11:57.800 --> 12:00.220
We are still up 40 bucks,

12:00.220 --> 12:03.514
and all from selling stuff
that nobody is gonna miss.

12:03.514 --> 12:05.475
High five.

12:05.475 --> 12:07.685
Dylan: Ugh!
What happened to the flat iron?!

12:07.685 --> 12:08.895
Who cares?
Your mom doesn't use it.

12:08.895 --> 12:10.438
No, <i>she</i> doesn't!

12:10.438 --> 12:11.648
Oh, God!

12:11.648 --> 12:13.316
How many alpacas
does this place have?

12:13.316 --> 12:14.359
Look away!

12:14.359 --> 12:17.737
"Is that
how your hair is?"

12:17.737 --> 12:19.113
I'm my curly haired mother's
daughter!

12:20.365 --> 12:21.866
Who has my hat?!

12:21.866 --> 12:25.286
Oh, that...
could be anybody.

12:25.286 --> 12:27.830
A... heavy‐set woman
with Nevada plates.

12:28.957 --> 12:30.250
Ugh!

12:30.250 --> 12:32.168
"Oh, no.

12:32.168 --> 12:37.173
At last, your true vanity
is revealed."

12:37.173 --> 12:39.008
Just like
that evil robot said.

12:39.008 --> 12:40.593
Ray and Raja,
give me back my life!

12:40.593 --> 12:41.636
[ Door opens ]

12:41.636 --> 12:43.930
Good morning, everyone.

12:43.930 --> 12:46.099
Did you sleep well
in the beds that I arranged?

12:46.099 --> 12:47.558
Pack up, Ray.
We're leaving.

12:47.558 --> 12:48.935
Why?
You lied.

12:48.935 --> 12:50.561
You hijacked
our vacation.

12:50.561 --> 12:52.605
This family
has a tradition,

12:52.605 --> 12:55.316
and you may think it's stupid,
but it's <i>ours.</i>

12:55.316 --> 12:57.860
Today, we go back to it
<i>our</i> way.

12:57.860 --> 12:59.362
Where are my yoga pants?

12:59.362 --> 13:00.905
[ Scoffs ] Don't tell me
you actually wear those.

13:00.905 --> 13:02.240
Yeah!
I have to find them.

13:02.240 --> 13:03.574
Do you have any idea
how much they cost?

13:03.574 --> 13:05.076
Uh...

13:05.076 --> 13:06.953
one price could be $6?

13:06.953 --> 13:08.454
But what's our plan?

13:08.454 --> 13:09.789
Maya: I only know
what we're <i>not</i> doing ‐‐

13:09.789 --> 13:12.166
hot‐air ballooning,
panning for gold.

13:12.166 --> 13:14.085
How do you know
my itinerary?

13:14.085 --> 13:16.212
It hasn't even
left my sight.

13:16.212 --> 13:17.046
"Checkmate!"

13:18.548 --> 13:20.049
[ Laughs evilly ]

13:20.049 --> 13:21.342
♪♪

13:21.342 --> 13:24.262
[ Indistinct conversations ]

13:24.262 --> 13:26.848
... and I pull to my stop sign,
this car comes out of nowhere ‐‐

13:29.058 --> 13:30.727
And I'm like,
can you not read?

13:30.727 --> 13:33.313
It says "Stop"!
Yeah!

13:33.313 --> 13:35.815
Kenneth.
Where are you going?

13:35.815 --> 13:38.860
Oh, I, uh, I have
a very important meeting.

13:38.860 --> 13:42.071
Me too ‐‐ Lunch meeting.
No time to stop.

13:42.071 --> 13:44.407
[ Chuckles ]

13:44.407 --> 13:47.410
I‐I'm actually gonna
go eat in my car.

13:47.410 --> 13:49.662
Well, I'm gonna...
eat in my office.

13:50.913 --> 13:53.207
Would...you like
to go eat in my car?

13:53.207 --> 13:56.044
I think it would make more sense
for us to eat in my office.

13:56.044 --> 13:57.837
Ah. Yeah.

13:57.837 --> 13:58.838
[ Chuckles ]

13:58.838 --> 14:00.465
Mm.

14:00.465 --> 14:02.091
It's funny ‐‐

14:02.091 --> 14:03.426
without my little guy
to hide behind,

14:03.426 --> 14:04.927
I don't belong anywhere.

14:04.927 --> 14:07.221
I'm not a student,
I'm not a teacher.

14:07.221 --> 14:09.390
Where do
the aides hang out?

14:09.390 --> 14:11.142
Um, hello.

14:11.142 --> 14:12.685
Where do the principals
hang out?

14:12.685 --> 14:14.520
How about that?

14:14.520 --> 14:16.773
You're one of a kind,
too.

14:16.773 --> 14:18.733
We're like
a couple of snowflakes.

14:18.733 --> 14:21.027
The Snowflake Society.

14:21.027 --> 14:22.361
Because we're unique

14:22.361 --> 14:25.198
and we're so cool,
we're cold.

14:25.198 --> 14:26.240
[ Both laugh ]

14:27.575 --> 14:30.244
You know, Snowflake,
every day after school,

14:30.244 --> 14:31.662
I go to my favorite spot

14:31.662 --> 14:33.623
and help myself
to a salted caramel macchiato.

14:33.623 --> 14:35.166
Ooh.

14:35.166 --> 14:36.751
Do you know the grass patch
behind the shop building?

14:36.751 --> 14:38.211
Yeah, I know it well.

14:38.211 --> 14:39.587
Would you care
to join me?

14:39.587 --> 14:40.755
Sure.

14:40.755 --> 14:41.756
See you after school.

14:41.756 --> 14:42.924
[ Chuckles ]

14:42.924 --> 14:45.635
Ooh! Secret handshake!

14:45.635 --> 14:47.303
All right, yeah.
Sure, sure, sure.

14:47.303 --> 14:48.471
Something like that.

14:48.471 --> 14:50.098
[ Chuckles ]

14:50.098 --> 14:51.808
All right, kids,
back on track.

14:51.808 --> 14:52.892
Which way now?

14:52.892 --> 14:54.310
[ Groaning ]
I don't feel good.

14:54.310 --> 14:56.437
Oh, Ray, we're not
falling for that.

14:56.437 --> 14:58.815
Stop for antacids,
end up in some aquarium.

14:58.815 --> 15:00.566
No, thanks very much.

15:00.566 --> 15:03.361
Don't just start driving!
My plan is great!

15:03.361 --> 15:05.863
Just enough structure,
but you'll still feel free.

15:05.863 --> 15:07.865
It's the way I imagine
a great bra feels like.

15:07.865 --> 15:10.284
It is <i>precisely</i> what a great bra
feels like, Ray,

15:10.284 --> 15:11.869
and you don't
get to have it.

15:11.869 --> 15:13.621
[ Moans ]

15:13.621 --> 15:15.665
Darling?
Are you all right?

15:15.665 --> 15:17.250
[ Panting ]

15:17.250 --> 15:18.668
Dylan:
"Don't believe him.

15:18.668 --> 15:20.419
We'll all be
touching sea slugs."

15:20.419 --> 15:21.420
Yeah.

15:21.420 --> 15:23.089
You don't look well
at all.

15:23.089 --> 15:24.257
Either you're really good
at faking

15:24.257 --> 15:25.550
or your appendix
is about to ‐‐

15:25.550 --> 15:26.759
[ Moans ]

15:26.759 --> 15:28.386
Jimmy, hospital ‐‐ now!

15:28.386 --> 15:30.263
[ Strained ]
Freeway's to the left!

15:30.263 --> 15:31.430
Wrong way!

15:31.430 --> 15:32.932
Are you still
ignoring me?

15:32.932 --> 15:34.100
Jimmy:
I'm sorry. It's habit.

15:38.437 --> 15:40.314
We'll run some tests,
but I assure you,
it's most likely gas.

15:40.314 --> 15:42.608
Yeah, lady, this is not
our first emergency room.

15:42.608 --> 15:45.278
Now, we can do the whole
"It's just gas" song and dance,

15:45.278 --> 15:46.612
but you're better off
just trusting my wife.

15:47.738 --> 15:49.574
Now, which side
is the discomfort on?

15:49.574 --> 15:51.284
It's on
the bloody appendix side.

15:51.284 --> 15:53.327
Go on, darling,
do your little trick.

15:53.327 --> 15:54.745
[ Groans loudly ]

15:54.745 --> 15:56.289
Okay.
A few questions ‐‐

15:56.289 --> 15:58.541
No past surgeries,
he's allergic to penicillin,

15:58.541 --> 16:01.294
blood type AB positive,
and 115 pounds.

16:01.294 --> 16:03.129
Thanks for
the extra 5 pounds.

16:03.129 --> 16:04.505
You're very welcome,
my darling.

16:04.505 --> 16:06.757
We'll need to contact
your pediatrician for ‐‐

16:06.757 --> 16:07.800
I have his records.

16:07.800 --> 16:09.886
You have my records?

16:09.886 --> 16:11.762
You're not the only Ray
in this family, Ray.

16:11.762 --> 16:13.306
It's color‐coded?

16:13.306 --> 16:14.724
And the labels?

16:14.724 --> 16:16.392
And the white background,
even?

16:16.392 --> 16:19.020
Well, of course, 'cause
if you use the clear ones,

16:19.020 --> 16:20.813
it's not legible
on a dark surface.
... not legible
on a dark surface.

16:22.732 --> 16:24.734
[ Groans loudly ]

16:24.734 --> 16:26.611
How did you get
the little squiggly

16:26.611 --> 16:28.696
on top of the "n"
in "Dr. Nuñez"?

16:28.696 --> 16:30.323
Oh, darling,
don't worry.

16:31.365 --> 16:33.326
You have to go into Settings.
I'll show you, yeah.

16:33.326 --> 16:35.203
Woman on P. A.
<i>Dr. Alvarez to O. R. 2.</i>

16:35.203 --> 16:37.663
How are you so calm?
He seems awful.

16:37.663 --> 16:39.665
Look at
this last fortune ‐‐

16:39.665 --> 16:42.210
"Your family will suffer
a shattering loss."

16:42.210 --> 16:43.544
Ray's gonna die!

16:43.544 --> 16:44.754
Wait! What?!

16:44.754 --> 16:46.172
Different Ray!

16:46.172 --> 16:47.173
[ Laughs nervously ]
You're good.

16:49.467 --> 16:51.344
Oh, God.

16:51.344 --> 16:53.346
JJ, when you're
in the hospital,

16:53.346 --> 16:54.847
what does Dad tell you
to make you feel better?

16:55.681 --> 16:58.601
Jimmy: "Ray could not
handle this."

16:59.727 --> 17:01.020
I can see
how that would help.

17:03.189 --> 17:05.983
"You got this.
No doubt."

17:13.282 --> 17:14.742
I've spent a lot of time
in hospitals.

17:14.742 --> 17:17.328
I want to lay something out
for you.

17:17.328 --> 17:19.455
You repeat it,
I'll deny.

17:19.455 --> 17:22.708
You ‐‐ Ray, okay ‐‐

17:22.708 --> 17:26.254
...do not get to have
anything go wrong with you.

17:26.254 --> 17:29.048
Sorry. Not interested.
Understood?

17:29.048 --> 17:30.675
Okay.

17:30.675 --> 17:32.051
Okay.

17:32.051 --> 17:34.679
You go show that appendix
who's boss.

17:34.679 --> 17:37.098
Okay, darling, I'm gonna talk
to the surgeon first.

17:37.098 --> 17:38.975
If I don't like anything
that I see,

17:38.975 --> 17:40.560
I'm gonna perform it
myself.

17:40.560 --> 17:42.061
Okay?
That's a promise.

17:42.061 --> 17:43.396
[ Smooches ]

17:43.396 --> 17:46.691
I'm so sorry
I was such a crappy sister.

17:46.691 --> 17:48.651
I'm gonna miss you
so much!

17:48.651 --> 17:50.528
Why did she
have to go last?!

17:56.325 --> 17:59.954
[ Cellphone rings ]

17:59.954 --> 18:01.372
Hello?

18:01.372 --> 18:02.582
Kenneth, where the hell
have you been?!

18:02.582 --> 18:03.749
I've been calling you
for an hour!

18:03.749 --> 18:05.585
Ahhhh! Maya.

18:05.585 --> 18:07.378
I didn't realize how much
I've missed your screech.

18:07.378 --> 18:08.754
[ Sighs ]

18:08.754 --> 18:10.756
Ray's in the hospital.
Could you bring me a few things?

18:10.756 --> 18:12.633
What?
Oh, of course.

18:12.633 --> 18:13.676
Yeah, I'm on my way.

18:13.676 --> 18:14.927
But I haven't told you
what I need,

18:14.927 --> 18:16.053
and you don't know
where we are.

18:16.053 --> 18:17.346
I'm exiting the school!

18:17.346 --> 18:19.140
You're not in the school,
correct?

18:19.140 --> 18:21.225
I've missed this.
You have no idea.

18:21.225 --> 18:23.853
♪♪

18:23.853 --> 18:25.646
He'll come.

18:29.859 --> 18:31.986
[ Exhales shakily ]

18:31.986 --> 18:36.198
Oh, the things some people
will do to take down a vacation.

18:38.492 --> 18:39.535
I made it.

18:39.535 --> 18:41.287
You did.

18:41.287 --> 18:43.247
Cheated the odds.

18:43.247 --> 18:45.374
I've got a few things
to show you.

18:45.374 --> 18:47.376
You're gonna be here
for a few days in recovery,

18:47.376 --> 18:49.045
so the trip ends here.

18:49.045 --> 18:50.671
But as per
your itinerary...

18:50.671 --> 18:52.840
rubber band ball.

18:52.840 --> 18:55.343
You said you wanted
the biggest one in the state.

18:55.343 --> 18:57.637
You woke up too fast
for me to make that,

18:57.637 --> 18:59.680
but I'm guessing this is one of
the bigger ones in the hospital.

18:59.680 --> 19:01.807
I love it.

19:01.807 --> 19:03.142
You know how you wanted
to pan for gold?

19:04.852 --> 19:06.937
This was
my grandpa's watch.

19:06.937 --> 19:08.606
It's yours now.

19:10.775 --> 19:12.193
Thank you.

19:12.193 --> 19:15.738
You were so good
back there.

19:15.738 --> 19:18.032
So...
Brave. Strong. Loving.

19:18.032 --> 19:20.117
Better.
[ Chuckles ]

19:20.117 --> 19:21.369
Organized.

19:22.703 --> 19:25.373
Where do you think
you get it?

19:25.373 --> 19:27.333
I'm that way
for the stuff that matters.

19:27.333 --> 19:30.044
And I have a lot
that matters ‐‐

19:30.044 --> 19:31.504
which is why
I have to let go

19:31.504 --> 19:33.297
and have fun
with the rest of it.

19:33.297 --> 19:34.882
We're not so different,
you and me.

19:38.594 --> 19:40.221
How do you feel?

19:40.221 --> 19:42.223
Kind of great.

19:42.223 --> 19:44.266
Mm.

19:44.266 --> 19:47.019
Oh, they gave you
the 115‐pound dose.

19:47.019 --> 19:48.729
It's probably enough
to knock out two of you.

19:48.729 --> 19:50.272
[ Laughs sleepily ]

19:52.066 --> 19:54.568
You know how you wanted
to go to the zoo?

19:57.279 --> 19:58.864
This is a lion.

19:58.864 --> 20:00.199
Rawr.

20:00.199 --> 20:03.536
Ooh! You've got
a feisty one.

20:03.536 --> 20:06.080
Yeeeeah.

20:08.332 --> 20:09.083
Good lion.

20:14.004 --> 20:15.172
So, thanks to the surgery,
you're hundreds of dollars

20:15.172 --> 20:16.757
in the hole,
but you're happy,

20:16.757 --> 20:20.594
'cause you get to have something
literally no human being needs?

20:20.594 --> 20:22.847
Best...vacation...ever.

20:22.847 --> 20:25.391
Oh, darling, Ray lived ‐‐

20:25.391 --> 20:29.228
which means we still owe Raja
one shattering loss.

20:29.228 --> 20:31.605
I don't care.
That stuff is baloney.

20:32.565 --> 20:33.399
For real.

20:38.571 --> 20:40.781
Oh, ow! Ow!

20:40.781 --> 20:41.782
[ Dylan laughs ]

20:41.782 --> 20:42.616
"Oops."

20:42.616 --> 20:43.701
You believe.

20:45.953 --> 20:48.205
Oh, my gosh!
Ray's baby is loose!

20:48.205 --> 20:49.707
Aaaaaaaaaaah!
